<br>&nbsp;<br>

<p>The <b>Two-Point Line</b> command enables you to create a line by specifying two through points. <br>&nbsp;
<table>
<tr valign="top">
<td>In the <b>Type</b> drop-down list you can choose the line extension as <b>Limited</b>, <b>Semilimited</b> or <b>Unlimited</b>.</td>
<td><IMG border=1 SRC="../../../../images/geometry/gm_01/2PointLineType.gif"></td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>In the <b>Sequence</b> drop-down list you can choose whether to create <b>Single</b> or <b>Multiple</b> lines.</td>
<td><IMG border=1 SRC="../../../../images/geometry/gm_01/2PointLineSequence.gif"></td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
<td>Alternatively to entering the two points, you can specify the line components relative to a polar or a Cartesian reference (select the reference in the <b>Option</b> drop-down list). Use <b>TAB</b> to move from a mini-dialog box to the next one and confirm the values you entered. When you're done, press <b>ENTER</b>. </td>
<td><IMG border=1 SRC="../images/2PointLineOption.gif"></td>
</tr>
</table>

